# Byte-exact assets - never EOL-convert (bytes are load-bearing: goldens, ROMs,
# disks, SRAM, frame/audio captures). `binary` == `-text -diff`.
#
# M54/DEC-0081: these pins match git's existing auto-detection, so adding them is
# INERT -- zero renormalization, zero churn to the existing Windows checkout.
# A blanket `* text=auto` / `eol=lf` is deliberately NOT set: it would renormalize
# the CRLF-committed text files and churn that checkout (a DEC-0081 hard
# requirement violation). Mixed CRLF/LF in text sources compiles cleanly under
# both MSVC and AppleClang, so nothing forces normalization.
*.rom   binary
*.dsk   binary
*.sram  binary
*.bin   binary
*.dump  binary
*.frame binary
*.png   binary
*.wav   binary
*.ico   binary

# Shell scripts must check out with LF on every platform or the shebang breaks
# (`bad interpreter: /usr/bin/env bash^M`). This is LOAD-BEARING, not a
# precaution: the repo now tracks several .sh files that run on macOS, Linux and
# the Raspberry Pi -- setup/build.sh, setup/kiosk/{launch,install-kiosk}.sh and
# the tools/capture/*.sh harnesses. A CRLF checkout of any of them fails at the
# shebang with an error that points at the interpreter rather than the line
# endings, which is exactly the kind of thing that wastes an afternoon.
*.sh    text eol=lf
